						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Vīrakumāra-Kampaṇa Uḍaiyar.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Virōdhikṛit, Āshāḍha, śu. 11.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Registers the royal order remitting the taxes on the village Paṭṭippulam in Āyiravēlip-paṟṟu in favour of the temple of Mudalīśvaram-Uḍaiya-Nāyaṉār at Kāliṅgarāyarūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Taḻuvakkuḻaindāṉ-nallūr, which was separated from Śiṟudāvūr, to provide for worship and repairs in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
